348,"user":{"displayName":"Taanush abraham","userId":"16497560746847074205"}},"outputId":"fe6ee94a-8bcb-44b6-d9d9-de50bd7de575"},"source":["# Solution\n","def isogram(w):\n","  for i in w:\n","    if w.count(i)!=0:\n","      c=1\n","  if c!=1:\n","    print('Not an isogram')\n","  else:\n","    print('It is an isogram')\n","isogram('Inti')"],"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["It is an isogram\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"PLSY4nu0UzCj"},"source":["In the above program, we have checked whether the count of any letter in the text is greater than 1 by using the `count()` function in an `if` condition.\n","\n","If the `if` condition is `True` in any of the cases, the message `The word is not isogram` is returned and the execution stops, otherwise the message `The word is isogram` is returned."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ftOXrP5NUzsZ"},"source":["---"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"BVT9G_baB1aq"},"source":["#### Activity 2: Does the Cargo Fit?\n","\n","A ship has to transport cargo from one place to another, while picking up cargo along the way. Given the total amount of cargo and the types of cargo holds in the ship as lists, create a function (let's say `will_fit()`) that returns `True` if each weight of cargo can fit in one hold, and `False` if it can't.\n","\n","- \"S\" means 50 cargo space.\n","\n","- \"M\" means 100 cargo space.\n","\n","- \"L\" means 200 cargo space.\n","\n","\n","**Examples**\n","```\n","1. will_fit([\"M\", \"L\", \"L\", \"M\"], [56, 62, 84, 90]) ➞ True\n","\n","2. will_fit([\"S\", \"S\", \"S\", \"S\", \"L\"], [40, 50, 60, 70 , 80, 90, 200]) ➞ False\n","\n","3. will_fit([\"L\", \"L\", \"M\"], [56, 62, 90]) ➞ True\n","\n","```\n","**Hint:** Use dictionary with `S`, `M` and `L` as keys and their respective cargo spaces as values. Calculate total space available in the ship and the total cargos to be shipped and compare them."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"0pIGxKG9B3mb","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1698413862841,"user_tz":-240,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"Taanush abraham","userId":"16497560746847074205"}},"outputId":"b398b3fc-f8d4-449a-e2c9-183c5298d1de"},"source":["# Solution\n","size={'S':50,'M':100,'L':200}\n","def will_fit(holds,cargo):\n","  total_space=0\n","  total_cargo=0\n","  for i in holds:\n","    total_space+=size[i]\n","  for j in cargo:\n","    total_cargo+=j;\n","  if total_space>=total_cargo:\n","    return True\n","  else:\n","    return False\n","print(will_fit([\"M\", \"L\", \"L\", \"M\"], [56, 62, 84, 90]))\n","will_fit([\"S\", \"S\", \"S\", \"S\", \"L\"], [40, 50, 60, 70 , 80, 90, 200])"],"execution_count":10,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["True\n"]},{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["False"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":10}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"z2vDEItoB8yW"},"source":["In the above program, first we have created a dictionary with `S`, `M` and `L` as keys and their respective cargo spaces as values.\n","\n","1. We have created the function `will_fit()` and have passed the `holds` (space in the ship) and `cargo` (number of cargos to be shipped) as parameters to this function.\n","\n","2. Inside this function, we have intialized two variables `totalSpace` and `totalCargo` with value `0` that indicates the total space available in ship and the total cargos to be shipped respectively.\n","\n","3. Using a `for` loop, we have traversed through the elements in `hold` parameter and have added their respective values in `totalSpace` variable.\n","\n","4. Similarly, we have added the cargos to be shipped in `totalCargo` variable one by one using another `for` loop.\n","\n","5. Finally, `True` is returned if the condition `totalCargo <= totalSpace` is satisfied, else `False` is returned.  \n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"IJIZASayCpEW"},"